Barely hours after deputy president William Ruto and his allies in the united democratic alliance, UDA maintained they will not be coerced to leave the Jubilee party, their jubilee counterparts now want action taken against them for associating with another party. The jubilee leaders are now planning to hold their own handshake allied pg in a week's time to deliberate on key issues facing the country. And as Daniel Kariuki reports, the kieleweke faction maintains they still have the numbers to push the government's agenda.
